For a more complete understanding of the present invention, reference is now made to the following descriptions taken in conjunction with the accompanying drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 illustrates a prior art heat sink and printed circuit or wiring board assembly;


FIG. 2A illustrates an embodiment of the heat sink constructed in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 2B illustrates a cross section view of the heat sink of FIG. 2A illustrating a double drawn support shoulder and button shoulder formed from the heat sink material;


FIG. 3A illustrates a heat sink constructed in accordance with the present invention associated with a circuit board;


FIG. 3B illustrates a cross section view of the heat sink inserted into an opening formed in a circuit board;


FIG. 4A illustrates a tool for flaring shoulder buttons on the heat sink to secure it to the circuit board;


FIG. 4B illustrates the flaring tool positioned so that the shoulder buttons can be flared to secure the heat sink to a circuit board; and


FIG. 4C illustrates a cross section view of the heat sink frictionally attached to a circuit board.
